data.contentText:
Care must be given to thermoregulation as per preterm guidelines

Remember to perform Ballard Score- images are first Neuromuscular followed by Physical maturity assessment

metadata.text1:
Position the airway & suction
If sats < 90% put on oxygen
If distress is significant & > 1kg consider CPAP according to the TRY CPAP algorithm.
Consult Iliff handbook for how to give CPAP
metadata.text2:
- If breathing 60-80 bpm use cup/OGT
- If needing CPAP use OGT
- If breathing > 80 bpm consider IV fluids
metadata.text3:
Antibiotics are recommended in all preterms with RDS

Give x pen 50000 units BD and gentamicin 4mg/kg OD (if <2000g)
metadata.title3: 3. Get IV access and start antibiotics

data.title: MANAGEMENT
